good
time.
We
will
have
a
little
reading
in
the
evening.
The
moon
rises
at
half
past
eight,
and
I
will
walk
up
to
the
rectory
with
you
at
nine.
Do
you
agree?"
She
nodded
her
head,
and
her
eyes
lit
up.
Moore
lingered
yet
two
minutes.
He
bent
over
Caroline's
desk
and
glanced
at
her
grammar,
he
fingered
her
pen,
he
lifted
her
bouquet
and
played
with
