that
Caroline
had
not
yet
commenced
her
exercise.
Mademoiselle
Moore
had
that
morning
a
somewhat
absent
minded
pupil.
Caroline
forgot,
again
and
again,
the
explanations
which
were
given
to
her.
However,
she
still
bore
with
unclouded
mood
the
chidings
her
inattention
brought
upon
