Sitting
in
the
sunshine
near
the
window,
she
seemed
to
receive
with
its
warmth
a
kind
influence,
which
made
her
both
happy
and
good.
Thus
disposed,
she
looked
her
best,
and
her
best
was
a
pleasing
vision.
To
her
had
not
been
denied
the
gift
of
beauty.
It
was
not
absolutely
necessary
to
know
her
in
order
to
like
her;
she
was
fair
enough
to
please,
even
at
the
first
